1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:03,740
(Final Episode)

2
00:00:06,340 --> 00:00:07,510
Oh Jang Mi,

3
00:00:07,510 --> 00:00:09,450
everything would have been fine
if it weren't for you.

4
00:00:09,850 --> 00:00:11,380
You're the cause of all this.

5
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,200
No, Jun Ho.

6
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:05,200
How...

7
00:01:06,140 --> 00:01:07,140
could this be...

8
00:01:12,110 --> 00:01:13,710
You hit my son?

9
00:01:14,380 --> 00:01:15,380
You?

10
00:01:17,020 --> 00:01:19,380
No.

11
00:01:22,350 --> 00:01:23,390
Jun Ho, no.

12
00:01:23,620 --> 00:01:25,720
Jun Ho...

13
00:01:26,620 --> 00:01:28,630
Jun Ho. It's me, your mom.

14
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:31,160
What are you doing on the ground?

15
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:32,300
Wake up.

16
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:34,230
I made a mistake.

17
00:01:35,230 --> 00:01:37,470
So open your eyes.

18
00:01:37,470 --> 00:01:39,000
Please, open your eyes.

19
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:41,070
Jun Ho. It's Dad.

20
00:01:43,510 --> 00:01:46,310
Please wake up. Come on. Jun Ho.

21
00:01:47,850 --> 00:01:49,450
Yes, that's it.

22
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:52,220
No matter what anyone says, you're my son.

23
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:56,090
- Please, wake up. Come on.
- Is Jang Mi...

24
00:01:58,120 --> 00:01:59,490
okay?

25
00:02:00,060 --> 00:02:01,190
I was wrong.

26
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:04,460
It's all my fault.

27
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:09,530
Please just stay alive. Please.

28
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:13,610
Jun Ho, no.

29
00:02:14,310 --> 00:02:15,370
Jun Ho.

30
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:17,480
Jun Ho!

31
00:02:18,740 --> 00:02:19,880
- Jun Ho, open your eyes.
- Jun Ho.

32
00:02:19,980 --> 00:02:23,750
Open your eyes. No, Jun Ho, my son.

33
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:26,220
Jun Ho!

34
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:30,320
This can't be happening.
This can't be, Jun Ho.

35
00:02:33,690 --> 00:02:37,160
I'm so sorry, Jun Ho.

36
00:02:37,330 --> 00:02:39,830
- Jun Ho, no, open your eyes.
- Baek Ho.

37
00:02:40,430 --> 00:02:42,030
What do I do?

38
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:47,140
Did I kill you with my own hands?
No. This can't be.

39
00:02:47,140 --> 00:02:48,270
Baek Ho.

40
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:51,480
Baek Ho, please wake up.

41
00:02:51,980 --> 00:02:53,110
What do I do?

42
00:02:54,950 --> 00:02:57,580
Are you awake? Baek Ho.

43
00:03:00,350 --> 00:03:01,720
Baek Ho!

44
00:03:02,250 --> 00:03:03,520
Baek Ho!

45
00:03:04,990 --> 00:03:06,020
No.

46
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:09,690
Baek Ho, wake up!

47
00:03:11,460 --> 00:03:12,530
No.

48
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:16,030
- Baek Ho, open your eyes.
- Jun Ho...

49
00:03:18,070 --> 00:03:19,840
Baek Ho, open your eyes.

50
00:03:21,110 --> 00:03:23,310
(Surgery in Progress)

51
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:32,320
Please.

52
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:35,020
Please, save my Baek Ho.

53
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:38,220
He's such a kind, decent man.

54
00:03:39,220 --> 00:03:43,030
He got hurt saving me.

55
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:44,730
You know that, don't you?

56
00:03:45,230 --> 00:03:46,500
You know that...

57
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,200
Baek Ho is completely innocent.

58
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,140
Please, save him.

59
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,070
It should've been me.
I should be the one who's dying.

60
00:03:57,380 --> 00:03:59,140
(Operating Room)

61
00:04:00,310 --> 00:04:01,380
Jang Mi.

62
00:04:02,050 --> 00:04:05,080
Mom. Baek Ho...

63
00:04:05,420 --> 00:04:07,750
Baek Ho got hurt because of me.

64
00:04:08,050 --> 00:04:09,820
(Operating Room)

65
00:04:11,020 --> 00:04:12,090
It's okay.

66
00:04:12,790 --> 00:04:14,130
Baek Ho will be fine.

67
00:04:14,830 --> 00:04:18,030
No matter what happens,
Baek Ho will wake up.

68
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,800
Don't you worry.

69
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:23,200
- Oh no...
- Mom.

70
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,970
It's because of me that Baek Ho is hurt.

71
00:04:27,070 --> 00:04:30,410
What if something happens to him
because of me, Mom?

72
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:34,950
Tae Pyung,
you should go check on Mrs. Han.

73
00:04:36,010 --> 00:04:37,520
She must be going through a lot right now.

74
00:04:38,550 --> 00:04:39,550
Okay.

75
00:04:40,950 --> 00:04:43,120
(Operating Room)

76
00:04:49,060 --> 00:04:50,260
We did everything we could,

77
00:04:51,030 --> 00:04:53,330
but Mr. Kang Jun Ho has passed away.

78
00:04:55,470 --> 00:04:56,470
Mrs. Han.

79
00:05:02,940 --> 00:05:04,280
What about Baek Ho?

80
00:05:06,140 --> 00:05:09,310
He's in emergency surgery right now.

81
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,750
My Jun Ho...

82
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:16,220
is gone.

83
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:20,290
I just...

84
00:05:21,490 --> 00:05:22,990
can't believe it.

85
00:05:25,430 --> 00:05:28,400
Why is this happening to me?

86
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:33,400
Wasn't stealing my husband enough?

87
00:05:35,270 --> 00:05:37,480
Why did she have to take my sons too?

88
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:43,280
Chae Hwa Young.

89
00:05:44,780 --> 00:05:46,280
That devilish witch.

90
00:05:48,690 --> 00:05:49,790
I should have just...

91
00:05:51,190 --> 00:05:53,730
killed her and gone to prison.

92
00:05:55,690 --> 00:05:57,100
Then...

93
00:05:57,260 --> 00:06:01,730
nothing would have happened to my sons.

94
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:13,850
Oh, my poor Jun Ho...

95
00:06:17,380 --> 00:06:18,520
Jun Ho.

96
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:22,020
Oh, my poor Baek Ho...

97
00:06:23,890 --> 00:06:28,690
I should have killed her.
I should have done it myself.

98
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,560
I...

99
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:33,600
I should have...

100
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:38,600
Mrs. Han!

101
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:40,300
Mrs. Han!

102
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:52,080
Hwa Young.

103
00:06:53,950 --> 00:06:54,950
Where's Jun Ho?

104
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:57,560
Why isn't he here?
We can't leave without him.

105
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,260
Please, snap out of it.

106
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:03,530
Are you crazy?
How can you call yourself his father?

107
00:07:03,830 --> 00:07:06,960
Why are we running away to save ourselves,
leaving our only son behind?

108
00:07:07,270 --> 00:07:09,870
This isn't right.
We have to go back and get Jun Ho.

109
00:07:10,470 --> 00:07:12,000
Go back where?

110
00:07:12,340 --> 00:07:14,140
The police are after us.
Where do you think you're going?

111
00:07:14,610 --> 00:07:16,770
We're just running to save ourselves
right now.

112
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,540
Snap out of it, Chae Hwa Young.

113
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:21,510
Jun Ho is dead.

114
00:07:22,910 --> 00:07:23,980
You...

115
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:25,980
killed him with your own hands.

116
00:07:27,050 --> 00:07:28,490
You killed your own son...

117
00:07:29,690 --> 00:07:30,990
with your own hands.

118
00:07:32,260 --> 00:07:34,660
Watch your mouth.
How could my Jun Ho be dead?

119
00:07:36,090 --> 00:07:39,100
He has to inherit Dream.
I'll make sure of it.

120
00:07:39,730 --> 00:07:42,030
I'm going to put my son at the very top.

121
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:44,140
I've dreamed of that for so long.

122
00:07:46,670 --> 00:07:47,740
Hwa Young.

123
00:07:49,610 --> 00:07:51,340
Let's hurry to the hotel, Manager Lee.

124
00:07:52,140 --> 00:07:54,450
I'll become the chairman
as soon as I get there.

125
00:07:54,710 --> 00:07:55,780
And then Jun Ho...

126
00:07:56,980 --> 00:07:58,180
Snap out of it.

127
00:07:58,620 --> 00:08:00,120
Jun Ho is dead!

128
00:08:05,490 --> 00:08:08,060
Hwa Young, if you fall apart,
what will we do?

129
00:08:08,860 --> 00:08:10,130
Please, get a grip.

130
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:13,200
If you're like this,
how are we supposed to survive?

131
00:08:14,630 --> 00:08:17,270
Jun Ho... What do I do?

132
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:20,710
What do I do about my poor Jun Ho?

133
00:08:21,770 --> 00:08:22,770
It's okay.

134
00:08:23,740 --> 00:08:25,840
It's okay. It was an accident.

135
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,820
As far as we're concerned,
nothing happened.

136
00:08:31,820 --> 00:08:34,890
It's okay. You just made a mistake.

137
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:37,620
I...

138
00:08:38,160 --> 00:08:40,690
I killed my Jun Ho with these hands.

139
00:08:41,790 --> 00:08:43,860
I killed my son, Jun Ho,

140
00:08:44,330 --> 00:08:46,160
who was my everything.

141
00:08:47,470 --> 00:08:50,500
Please forgive me.

142
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:56,710
I'll never, ever sin again,

143
00:08:56,810 --> 00:08:59,440
so please tell me my Jun Ho...

144
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,480
isn't dead.

145
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:03,750
- Tell me this was all a nightmare.
- Hwa Young.

146
00:09:08,390 --> 00:09:10,890
- Can you hear me?
- Wake up. It's Mom.

147
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,390
(Operating Room)

148
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:13,520
Baek Ho.

149
00:09:14,290 --> 00:09:17,090
Look at me, Baek Ho. Wake up.

150
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:19,130
You have to come back to me.

151
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:21,930
Can you hear me? Baek Ho.

152
00:09:22,770 --> 00:09:24,540
- Baek Ho.
- Baek Ho.

153
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:30,040
Mr. Kang Baek Ho has internal bleeding
from a ruptured cerebral blood vessel.

154
00:09:30,410 --> 00:09:32,040
We need to transfer him
to a larger hospital.

155
00:09:32,980 --> 00:09:33,980
I'm sorry.

156
00:09:39,650 --> 00:09:41,450
What in the world is going on?

157
00:09:42,490 --> 00:09:45,260
Bring me those evil bastards right now!

158
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:50,900
If anything happens to Baek Ho,
I'll kill them with my own two hands.

159
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:54,930
Get every man on this immediately
and find them!

160
00:09:55,870 --> 00:09:58,170
(Hanguk National University Hospital)

161
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:01,140
Tonight will likely be...

162
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,940
the most critical time.

163
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:07,350
You can't leave like this, Baek Ho.

164
00:10:08,110 --> 00:10:09,780
It's all my fault.

165
00:10:10,850 --> 00:10:13,280
I just assumed you'd always be by my side,

166
00:10:13,990 --> 00:10:17,250
so I complained and hurt your feelings.

167
00:10:18,020 --> 00:10:19,020
I'm sorry.

168
00:10:19,590 --> 00:10:20,660
I'm so sorry.

169
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:24,200
So please, just open your eyes.

170
00:10:25,030 --> 00:10:26,030
Baek Ho.

171
00:10:28,330 --> 00:10:29,900
I love you, Baek Ho.

172
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:47,550
We don't have time for this.
Let's go, quickly. The police are coming.

173
00:10:47,990 --> 00:10:48,990
No.

174
00:10:49,790 --> 00:10:51,560
I can't let Jun Ho go alone.

175
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:54,390
I have to go with him
so he won't be lonely.

176
00:10:56,890 --> 00:11:00,530
Oh Bok Gil and Seo Rin are coming.

177
00:11:03,770 --> 00:11:04,970
Jun Ho is coming too.

178
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,440
What's wrong with you?

179
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:09,510
I have to say I was wrong.
I have to beg for forgiveness.

180
00:11:09,610 --> 00:11:12,140
That's the only way Jun Ho
can go to a better place.

181
00:11:12,910 --> 00:11:15,710
- Hwa Young.
- His mother has to beg for forgiveness.

182
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:18,280
I can't let Jun Ho go alone.

183
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:20,750
Hwa Young.

184
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:22,890
Please, don't do this.

185
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:25,220
I'm holding it in too.

186
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:28,160
Even though I never once heard
Jun Ho call me Dad,

187
00:11:28,860 --> 00:11:29,860
and even though...

188
00:11:30,860 --> 00:11:33,360
I never got to hold him,
I'm keeping it together.

189
00:11:33,430 --> 00:11:34,430
Don't move!

190
00:11:34,930 --> 00:11:35,930
Put your hands up.

191
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,080
Jun Ho.

192
00:11:57,460 --> 00:11:58,460
Hwa Young!

193
00:12:01,660 --> 00:12:02,930
Surrender, Lee Kang Hyuk.

194
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:25,450
Lee Kang Hyuk. Drop the gun.

195
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:27,520
Send Hwa Young to me.

196
00:12:28,620 --> 00:12:29,790
Hwa Young, get over here.

197
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:34,060
I said hurry up!

198
00:12:34,460 --> 00:12:35,460
Jun Ho.

199
00:12:36,490 --> 00:12:39,230
Mom was wrong. It's all my fault.

200
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:44,000
I'll apologize to Jung Suk Hee
and Oh Jang Mi.

201
00:12:44,140 --> 00:12:45,900
Okay, Jun Ho?

202
00:12:49,770 --> 00:12:50,770
Lee Kang Hyuk.

203
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:52,610
Put the gun down.

204
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:05,520
Hwa Young.

205
00:13:06,490 --> 00:13:08,190
I'll go on ahead and wait for you.

206
00:13:28,410 --> 00:13:29,410
Lee Kang Hyuk.

207
00:13:30,950 --> 00:13:33,680
- Lee Kang Hyuk.
- Jun Ho, I'm sorry.

208
00:13:35,420 --> 00:13:36,490
I'm sorry.

209
00:13:38,020 --> 00:13:39,320
Jun Ho, I'm so sorry.

210
00:13:48,630 --> 00:13:49,730
Baek Ho.

211
00:13:51,070 --> 00:13:53,400
You can hear me, right?

212
00:13:54,340 --> 00:13:55,840
Open your eyes.

213
00:13:57,540 --> 00:13:59,510
You promised you'd grant my wish.

214
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:01,810
So you have to get up now.

215
00:14:02,910 --> 00:14:04,520
That's my wish.

216
00:14:05,350 --> 00:14:07,080
For you to open your eyes again...

217
00:14:07,590 --> 00:14:10,090
and smile at me.

218
00:14:10,990 --> 00:14:12,060
Okay?

219
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:14,260
You understand, Baek Ho?

220
00:14:14,830 --> 00:14:16,890
You have to keep your promise to me.

221
00:14:17,630 --> 00:14:18,660
Okay?

222
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:21,930
Baek Ho.

223
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:31,780
Baek Ho.

224
00:14:34,010 --> 00:14:35,180
Thank you.

225
00:14:35,810 --> 00:14:37,510
Thank you, Baek Ho.

226
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:39,750
Oh, thank you, Lord.

227
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:42,120
Thank you so much.

228
00:14:52,260 --> 00:14:56,430
(Three Months Later)

229
00:15:01,340 --> 00:15:02,670
What's going on?

230
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:05,880
Is no one here?

231
00:15:17,190 --> 00:15:18,220
Suk Hee.

232
00:15:24,060 --> 00:15:25,730
It took me...

233
00:15:26,260 --> 00:15:27,630
far too long to say this.

234
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:34,710
Will you marry me?

235
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:47,650
I'll make you so happy...

236
00:15:49,550 --> 00:15:50,920
that you'll forget...

237
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:54,060
all the hard times you've been through.

238
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:55,660
Dong Seok.

239
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:03,730
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations!

240
00:16:05,570 --> 00:16:06,970
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations!

241
00:16:08,470 --> 00:16:12,810
In the past, I opposed your marriage,
so this was delayed for far too long.

242
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:16,010
Now that you're starting over,

243
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:19,020
I'll give you the best wedding ever.

244
00:16:20,350 --> 00:16:21,850
Father, thank you.

245
00:16:22,420 --> 00:16:24,490
Thank you all so much.

246
00:16:25,690 --> 00:16:29,960
Grandma, this is a gift from Grandfather.

247
00:16:31,730 --> 00:16:35,570
- Dong Seok, what is this?
- These are the letters...

248
00:16:36,430 --> 00:16:38,440
I couldn't send you for 30 years.

249
00:16:40,170 --> 00:16:42,240
I wrote one whenever I missed you.

250
00:16:43,110 --> 00:16:45,680
And now, I can finally give them to you.

251
00:16:48,780 --> 00:16:49,950
Thank you.

252
00:16:50,680 --> 00:16:51,750
And...

253
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:53,780
I love you.

254
00:16:55,450 --> 00:16:56,890
A love confession.

255
00:16:57,190 --> 00:16:58,620
- Kiss.
- Kiss.

256
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:01,690
- Kiss.
- Kiss.

257
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:03,430
- Kiss.
- Kiss.

258
00:17:03,730 --> 00:17:05,000
Kiss.

259
00:17:07,030 --> 00:17:08,730
I think we're all ready to go.

260
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:12,040
Gosh, you're so good at your job,
CEO Kang.

261
00:17:12,100 --> 00:17:15,670
How did you even think of shooting
an introduction reel for the hotel?

262
00:17:15,870 --> 00:17:17,310
That's just the basics.

263
00:17:17,570 --> 00:17:20,310
Hotel management has to have
a modern flair these days, you know.

264
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:23,150
You've memorized your lines, right?
Let's get started.

265
00:17:24,180 --> 00:17:25,180
Okay.

266
00:17:26,850 --> 00:17:27,920
Hold on.

267
00:17:29,220 --> 00:17:32,260
Hi, I'm Ma Jang Mi,
the head chef at Dream Hotel,

268
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:34,390
and I'm about to introduce you
to our hotel.

269
00:17:34,390 --> 00:17:37,760
By myself? No, with our CEO.

270
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:40,030
What? Baek Ho.

271
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:42,100
Baek Ho...

272
00:17:43,030 --> 00:17:44,200
What?

273
00:17:44,740 --> 00:17:45,740
Baek Ho.

274
00:17:55,080 --> 00:17:56,610
What is this?

275
00:18:06,260 --> 00:18:07,260
Oh Jang Mi.

276
00:18:08,130 --> 00:18:09,360
Will you marry me?

277
00:18:13,330 --> 00:18:14,330
Of course.

278
00:18:15,530 --> 00:18:19,600
For me, you've always been my first man.

279
00:18:20,540 --> 00:18:23,410
If I don't marry you,
who else would I marry?

280
00:18:27,410 --> 00:18:28,550
Thank you, Jang Mi.

281
00:18:32,620 --> 00:18:35,720
I told you, right?
I'd get you a ring with a huge rock.

282
00:18:37,150 --> 00:18:40,220
When did you prepare all this?

283
00:20:01,540 --> 00:20:03,670
Yes, we're getting married!

284
00:20:05,710 --> 00:20:07,040
I love you, Kang Baek Ho!

285
00:20:07,310 --> 00:20:08,710
I love you, Oh Jang Mi!

286
00:20:12,350 --> 00:20:13,720
(The Late Kang Jun Ho)

287
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:15,720
(Jun Ho, I pray you find peace
wherever you are.)

288
00:20:15,720 --> 00:20:16,720
(Oh Jang Mi)

289
00:20:16,790 --> 00:20:20,820
Jun Ho.
I pray you find peace wherever you are.

290
00:20:21,930 --> 00:20:24,290
(The Late Lee Kang Hyuk,
The Late Kang Jun Ho)

291
00:20:24,290 --> 00:20:25,300
Lee Kang Hyuk.

292
00:20:25,930 --> 00:20:27,060
So in the end,

293
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:30,800
it's only in death that you can be
next to Jun Ho.

294
00:20:32,970 --> 00:20:34,040
Jun Ho.

295
00:20:37,040 --> 00:20:38,140
I love you.

296
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:40,910
(The Late Kang Jun Ho)

297
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:38,800
Case number 2026DO-13792.

298
00:21:39,540 --> 00:21:41,240
- The defendant, Chae Hwa Young,
- Let's eat.

299
00:21:41,340 --> 00:21:42,640
- has brutally violated the rule of law...
- Sound good?

300
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:44,840
and the right to life,

301
00:21:45,110 --> 00:21:47,440
the most fundamental of all human rights.

302
00:21:48,050 --> 00:21:50,910
It is therefore fitting to permanently
remove the defendant from society...

303
00:21:51,110 --> 00:21:54,690
and hold her strictly accountable
for her crimes.

304
00:21:55,820 --> 00:21:56,820
Judgment.

305
00:21:57,190 --> 00:21:58,660
- Jun Ho.
- The defendant, Chae Hwa Young,

306
00:21:58,820 --> 00:22:00,920
- Kang Hyuk.
- is sentenced to life in prison.

307
00:22:01,220 --> 00:22:02,290
Jun Ho.

308
00:22:02,490 --> 00:22:03,490
Kang Hyuk.

309
00:22:04,030 --> 00:22:05,100
Jun Ho.

310
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,360
Jun Ho.

311
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:09,400
Kang Hyuk. Jun Ho.

312
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:10,570
Kang Hyuk.

313
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:13,840
Jun Ho. Kang Hyuk.

314
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:16,070
Kang Hyuk...

315
00:22:18,980 --> 00:22:22,780
For so many young, aspiring chefs
across the country,

316
00:22:22,850 --> 00:22:26,120
you, Chef Ma, have become
the person they all want to be.

317
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:29,150
What's the secret to your success
in making...

318
00:22:29,150 --> 00:22:31,050
Dream Hotel's Korean Cuisine grow
so quickly?

319
00:22:31,460 --> 00:22:34,390
Well, my culinary journey
actually began...

320
00:22:34,490 --> 00:22:37,360
at my mother's small side dish shop.

321
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:39,400
I started by learning how to cater...

322
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:42,500
to the tastes and needs of customers...

323
00:22:42,570 --> 00:22:47,500
who came to buy the everyday side dishes
that we all have on our tables.

324
00:22:47,770 --> 00:22:49,140
I think those early experiences...

325
00:22:49,210 --> 00:22:50,340
(Recording)

326
00:22:50,410 --> 00:22:53,440
are the secret to why people
appreciate my cooking today.

327
00:22:57,580 --> 00:22:59,150
(CEO's Office)

328
00:22:59,250 --> 00:23:00,250
Chairman.

329
00:23:01,250 --> 00:23:03,250
Still working hard as ever, CEO Kang.

330
00:23:04,220 --> 00:23:06,160
When did you get back from Singapore?

331
00:23:06,660 --> 00:23:09,130
You were worried about
how busy Father was when you left.

332
00:23:09,330 --> 00:23:10,890
That's why I went for a quick visit.

333
00:23:11,460 --> 00:23:13,230
And there was some urgent business
at the company.

334
00:23:14,060 --> 00:23:17,900
But you're really starting to look
like a CEO now, my dear son-in-law.

335
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:19,640
Oh, please, you're always teasing me.

336
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:24,570
The rapid growth of Dream Hotel is
all thanks to you, Baek Ho.

337
00:23:25,180 --> 00:23:27,710
- Thank you, Baek Ho.
- Oh, please, Mother.

338
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:30,180
We're family. There's no need.

339
00:23:30,180 --> 00:23:32,680
Oh, right. Your father-in-law said that...

340
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:34,720
once he finished his work,
he'd come back to Korea...

341
00:23:34,790 --> 00:23:36,690
to see his grandchildren in person.

342
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:37,990
That's wonderful.

343
00:23:37,990 --> 00:23:40,590
Honey and Sweetie's first birthday
is coming up soon anyway.

344
00:23:41,690 --> 00:23:42,760
Baek Ho.

345
00:23:42,760 --> 00:23:43,860
Hi, Mom.

346
00:23:44,430 --> 00:23:46,300
Aren't you working too hard?

347
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:49,000
Mother, you need to scold Jang Mi.

348
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:51,870
She hasn't even fully recovered,
and she just rushed right back to work.

349
00:23:52,170 --> 00:23:54,540
I can't live if you're sick.
You know that, right?

350
00:23:54,540 --> 00:23:56,310
I know, dear.

351
00:23:56,470 --> 00:23:57,970
(CEO Kang Baek Ho)

352
00:23:58,410 --> 00:24:01,850
Secretary Jin.
Did the trip with my mom go well?

353
00:24:02,510 --> 00:24:07,320
Yes. And thank you so much
for forgiving me.

354
00:24:08,820 --> 00:24:12,190
I'm prepared to work myself to the bone.

355
00:24:12,190 --> 00:24:14,420
I promise I'll do my absolute best.

356
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:17,230
You must've learned now
what kind of trouble excessive greed...

357
00:24:17,730 --> 00:24:19,060
can cause.

358
00:24:19,730 --> 00:24:22,030
I'm counting on you.

359
00:24:23,130 --> 00:24:25,540
The piggies went "oink, oink"?

360
00:24:25,670 --> 00:24:29,740
You know, dreaming of pigs means
you're going to get some money.

361
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:33,710
Oh my, since you've been so polite,
I should give you some allowance.

362
00:24:34,310 --> 00:24:35,650
Yes!

363
00:24:35,650 --> 00:24:38,580
- How much will you give me?
- What? How much?

364
00:24:38,820 --> 00:24:42,990
- Bo Ra, don't be rude to Grandfather.
- It's fine.

365
00:24:43,250 --> 00:24:45,820
Are you off to sign
the opening contract with the hotel?

366
00:24:45,820 --> 00:24:47,020
Yes.

367
00:24:47,220 --> 00:24:49,630
When we open the premium shabu restaurant
at the hotel,

368
00:24:49,630 --> 00:24:51,490
please be our first customer, Chairman.

369
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:54,100
Of course I'll be your first customer.

370
00:24:55,770 --> 00:24:57,800
- Father, I'm back.
- Hey.

371
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:02,310
By the way, where is Mrs. Yeom?

372
00:25:02,310 --> 00:25:05,040
She's running around
saying she's Tae Pyung's manager.

373
00:25:05,040 --> 00:25:06,510
It's a whole spectacle.

374
00:25:09,050 --> 00:25:10,410
Hello.

375
00:25:11,750 --> 00:25:14,080
This is new singer Oh Tae Pyung.

376
00:25:14,150 --> 00:25:17,550
Hello. This is the up-and-coming
new singer, Oh Tae Pyung.

377
00:25:18,690 --> 00:25:21,090
For oceans, the Pacific.
For singers, Oh Tae Pyung.

378
00:25:21,090 --> 00:25:24,160
The rising star, Tae Pyung.

379
00:25:25,460 --> 00:25:27,700
- Please give him your support.
- Hey...

380
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:28,900
- Come here.
- Goodness.

381
00:25:29,170 --> 00:25:30,370
- Manager.
- Yes?

382
00:25:30,430 --> 00:25:32,870
I told you not to do promotions
at the hospital.

383
00:25:33,300 --> 00:25:35,140
You did the same thing
at the funeral home last time.

384
00:25:36,270 --> 00:25:37,870
But wouldn't it be great...

385
00:25:37,870 --> 00:25:41,510
if the patients here listened
to your songs and felt better?

386
00:25:42,350 --> 00:25:44,210
- No, that's...
- Go on, sing a song for us.

387
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:46,550
Oh my! Sing a song.

388
00:25:46,980 --> 00:25:51,450
- Thank you.
- How can I sing in a hospital?

389
00:25:51,890 --> 00:25:54,790
<i>Let's have a drink</i>

390
00:25:55,260 --> 00:25:58,230
<i>Let's party until we drop,</i>
<i>let's have a drink</i>

391
00:25:58,730 --> 00:26:00,500
(Happy First Birthday)

392
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:04,730
That kid's got the lungs of a general.

393
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:07,070
(Happy First Birthday, Honey and Sweetie.)

394
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:10,770
The kids are a perfect mix
of their mom and dad.

395
00:26:10,770 --> 00:26:11,910
Goodness.

396
00:26:11,910 --> 00:26:14,780
If you ask me,
they look just like their mother.

397
00:26:15,180 --> 00:26:18,110
What are you talking about?
Our Baek Ho is quite the looker himself.

398
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:21,350
That's because Baek Ho gets
his good looks from me.

399
00:26:21,950 --> 00:26:26,060
Oh, stop it. Baek Ho is
the complete opposite of you.

400
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:31,530
- Peekaboo, Sweetie.
- What? That's Honey.

401
00:26:32,130 --> 00:26:34,100
Daddy doesn't recognize Honey.

402
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:35,830
What are you talking about?
This is Sweetie.

403
00:26:35,900 --> 00:26:38,200
What kind of father can't even recognize
his own child?

404
00:26:38,370 --> 00:26:40,540
The one without the mole behind
the ear is Honey,

405
00:26:40,540 --> 00:26:41,910
and this one is Sweetie.

406
00:26:41,970 --> 00:26:42,970
Really?

407
00:26:44,570 --> 00:26:45,610
You're right.

408
00:26:48,040 --> 00:26:51,580
And now, it's time
for the fortune-picking ceremony.

409
00:26:55,020 --> 00:26:58,020
What will our twins choose, I wonder?

410
00:26:58,220 --> 00:27:01,320
Mom, what are you hoping they'll choose?

411
00:27:01,490 --> 00:27:04,690
I want them to be like their father,

412
00:27:05,430 --> 00:27:06,930
so I hope they pick the gavel
to live a just life.

413
00:27:07,260 --> 00:27:09,230
All right. The gavel is one suggestion.

414
00:27:09,530 --> 00:27:13,840
- Okay, and what about Dad?
- Well, I hope they'll be like their mom,

415
00:27:14,470 --> 00:27:16,310
- so, this one?
- What?

416
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:18,270
You think I'm about money?

417
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:20,510
It's Shin Saimdang.
A good wife and a wise mother.

418
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:22,680
Well, money is good too.

419
00:27:22,910 --> 00:27:25,720
Okay, let me go over here
for another interview.

420
00:27:25,850 --> 00:27:29,050
Grandfather,
what do you hope the twins will pick?

421
00:27:29,150 --> 00:27:32,860
Well, for them to be good students,
they should pick something like a pencil.

422
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:36,360
Oh, forget the pencil. It has to be money.

423
00:27:36,430 --> 00:27:38,400
Okay. She says money.

424
00:27:39,730 --> 00:27:42,900
Okay, Bo Ra.
What do you want them to pick?

425
00:27:43,130 --> 00:27:44,330
Jelly.

426
00:27:46,670 --> 00:27:49,170
- Jelly...
- And we have a vote for jelly.

427
00:27:49,240 --> 00:27:52,640
Now then, our Honey and Sweetie.

428
00:27:52,840 --> 00:27:55,010
What will they choose?

429
00:27:55,510 --> 00:27:58,650
- Go ahead and pick. Drumroll, please...
- Okay, let's see.

430
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:02,890
What are you going to grab?

431
00:28:02,990 --> 00:28:05,390
(Happy First Birthday, Honey and Sweetie.)

432
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:06,720
What will they pick?

433
00:28:08,460 --> 00:28:10,130
What will they pick?

434
00:28:12,330 --> 00:28:14,000
(Happy First Birthday, Honey and Sweetie.)

435
00:28:22,970 --> 00:28:24,070
Okay, here we go.

436
00:28:24,070 --> 00:28:26,210
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

437
00:28:29,710 --> 00:28:33,480
(Thank you for watching
and supporting The First Man.)

438
00:28:54,500 --> 00:28:56,510
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
